---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="hmdsamci - About">
    <div class="about-page">
        <h1>About</h1>

        <section>
            <h2>What is this?</h2>
            <p>
                hmdsamci (how many days since a major cybersecurity incident)
                tracks how many days have passed since a notable cybersecurity
                incident was reported
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Is this serious?</h2>
            <p>
                Unfortunately. I'm sure it'll be quite eye opening for some
                people
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Why is every link using Archive.is?</h2>
            <p>
                <a href="https://archive.is" target="_blank">Archive.is</a> is used to preserve the articles in their original
                form at time of writing and is also used to bypass any
                potentially paywalled articles
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>I can't access Archive.is!</h2>
            <p>
                Use an alternative - <a href="https://archive.li" target="_blank">Archive.li</a>
                or <a href="https://archive.ph" target="_blank">Archive.ph</a>. Simply
                change the .tld in the URL and it should work
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>What counts as a "major incident"?</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Data breaches affecting a significant number of people (e.g
                    credentials, PII)
                </li>
                <li>
                    Ransomware attacks on critical infrastructure or healthcare
                </li>
                <li>
                    Supply chain compromises with broad impact (A weekly
                    occurence at this rate)
                </li>
                <li>State sponsored attacks that are known to the public</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>What does not count?</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Routine phishing campaigns</li>
                <li>Individual account compromises</li>
                <li>Speculative / unconfirmed reports</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>How is this maintained?</h2>
            <p>
                I manually update this when I feel like it based on what news
                events I've come across or been sent. I could probably use something 
                like RSS feeds and automate it a bit but that could be more effort than 
                it's worth for now
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
            <blockquote>
                All incident descriptions are based on publicly available
                reporting. This site does not disclose any non-public
                information. Dates of incidents are based on when they were first reported,
                not the specific date they occurred
            </blockquote>
        </section>
    </div>
</Base>
